All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Broker
The Broker class represents a message broker that handles the communication between nodes of distributed system.
ElectionHandler
The ElectionHandler class implements the Handler and MessageListener interfaces and represents a handler for the election process in the distributed system.
Handler
The Handler interface represents a handler that can start and close a process or object.
MessageHandler
The MessageHandler interface provides methods for interacting with JMS messages.
MessageHandlerImpl
The MessageHandlerImpl class implements the Handler and MessageHandler interfaces and provides functionality for handling JMS messages.
Node
The Node class represents a node that interacts with other nodes in the distributed system.
NodesHandler
The NodesHandler class implements the Handler and MessageListener interfaces and represents a nodes handler in the distributed system.
Print
The Print class provides methods to print messages with different colors in the console.
RandomProb
The RandomProb class provides a method to generate a random boolean value based on a specified probability.
RequestHandler
The RequestHandler class represents a request handler object.
RequestType
The RequestType enum represents the types of requests that can be made.
ResourcesHandler
The ResourcesHandler class implements the Handler and MessageListener interfaces and represents a resources handler in the distributed system.
WaitResponse
The WaitResponse class represents a wait response object.
